01:02:51.030 --> 01:02:52.590
I've got other things to do.
 

01:02:52.590 --> 01:02:55.300
I've got to find a better way
to store energy.

01:02:55.300 --> 01:02:56.840
How do you shake hands with
people?

01:02:56.840 --> 01:02:58.519
So you have to find another way.
 

01:02:58.519 --> 01:02:59.809
So here's what you do.
 

01:02:59.809 --> 01:03:03.952
You take one conductor and you
take another conductor,

01:03:03.952 --> 01:03:07.079
any shape you like,
it doesn't matter.

01:03:07.079 --> 01:03:09.909
They are both electrically
neutral, but they're conductors.

01:03:09.909 --> 01:03:14.820
So you take a tiny charge from
this guy and put it there.

01:03:14.820 --> 01:03:18.949
Then take more and more charge
and start putting it there.

01:03:18.949 --> 01:03:21.387
At any stage,
when you stop,

01:03:21.387 --> 01:03:26.985
you will have a lot of positive
charges on this conductor and a

01:03:26.985 --> 01:03:31.139
lot of negative charges on this
conductor.

01:03:31.139 --> 01:03:34.164
This conductor will be at one
potential because it's a

01:03:34.164 --> 01:03:34.849
conductor.
 

01:03:34.849 --> 01:03:37.251
That conductor will be at
another potential because it's a

01:03:37.251 --> 01:03:39.150
conductor, but both have unique
potentials.

01:03:39.150 --> 01:03:42.045
They are not the same,
but this whole conductor has

01:03:42.045 --> 01:03:44.418
one potential,
this has another potential,

01:03:44.418 --> 01:03:45.230
